<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101581720497986></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101581720497986><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=13&mid=101581720497986>RE: Solo</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=13&mid=101581720497986#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=123295><span id= >dinathebeguiler</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>9 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Mar 10th 10:28 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Soloing is tough for a chanter, but instead of soloing completely consider teaming up with a Wizard, Mag, or Necro who can benefit from your mana buffs. The two of you can kite things together and you can still charm something to be your tank while the two of you nuke it down. I have done this several times and its a blast to do and quite refreshing from the usual 6 person group.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
