	   <tr><td colspan=2>Enchanters are not really known to be a solo class, but they can get away with soloing with the charm line.&nbsp;&nbsp;However, many of their spells and abilities work the best in group situations.  Some examples: clarity line helps all group members and allows faster pulling.  Haste helps your tanks kill faster and hence take less damage, which again allows faster pulling.  The mez line is most useful in groups since that is most likely the situation where you'll encounter more than one beast at a time.<br><br>For soloing, again charm is your greatest asset if you ask me.  Charm soloing is fun, challenging, and can be rewarding, but I don't know of any enchanters who have strictly or even mostly soloed throughout their career.  Some other helpful charm soloing spells are the slow line, nukes, and to a lesser extent your DoTs.<br><br>There's the slightly long answer.  The short answer, in my opinion, would be that enchanters are best suited to group situations but can also solo effectively in certain situations.  Personally, I would say I group 90% of the time and solo mainly for a break from the grind, for some added excitement, and to keep all of my skills up to snuff.<br><br>have fun,<br><br>-Yizz<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
