<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101579666596548></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101579666596548><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=13&mid=101579666596548>RE: new enthanter</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=13&mid=101579666596548#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=43653><span id=Scholar>GLASS</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>161 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Mar 10th 4:46 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.38]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>There is no one best race for enchanters or any class really.&nbsp;&nbsp;They all have their unique skills and defincicies.  That being said, I'll run down the list of 'Enchanterable' races and do a quick comparison.  Before that, though, I'll list in order what stats I believe to be most important to the class:<br><br>1)INT - Of course, more intelligence = more mana at each level.  As enchanters are a pure INT caster class, the importance of mana is hard to argue with.<br><br>2)CHA - Enchanters are unique in their charisma-based spells such as the charm and mezz line.  These are both pretty crucial skills to the clas and as such I would put CHA as the number 2 stat.<br><br>3)STA - Enchanters quite possibly take the most aggro of all caster classes when trying to get hairy situations under control.  STA adds to the number of hitpoints you get at every level.  Obviously, with more HP you can take more hits.  So, I put this stat at number 3.<br><br>4)STR - A large frustration I have found with the class is the inability to carry much loot after you have all of your gear equipped and on your person.  For this reason alone, I favor STR as the number 4 stat.<br><br>OK, with this order in mind I'll compare each race as far as stats and abilities go:<br><br>Dark Elf - INT 109, CHA 70, STA 65, STR 60.  Inkies start with good INT but the lowest CHA.  STA is also the lowest, and STR is average.<br><br>Advantages:  DEs can see at night with ultravision from the start.  Enchanters get vision enhancing spells which make this only a minor advantage.  I like that DEs start close to the center of Norrath, and as an agnostic enchanter can get into many cities from the beginning.  Again, though, faction is a minor issue to enchanters who get many spells to get them into otherwise hostile territory.<br><br>Disadvantages:  DEs are considered an evil race which may deter some players.  Their starting CHA is pretty stinky as well.<br><br>Erudite - INT 117, CHA 80, STA 70, STR 60.  Erudites start with the highest INT and second highest CHA scores.  Their STA and STR are also both decent.<br><br>Advantages:  Like already said, they get some really good starting stats to begin with.  Their starting faction is also pretty decent with many cities and races.<br><br>Disadvantages:  Erudites have no night vision to begin with, but again this will quickly change with spells.  Their starting area really sucks if you ask me too.<br><br>Gnome - INT 108, CHA 70, STA 70, STR 60.  Gnomes have good starting INT but tie for the lowest starting CHA with DEs.  Their STA and STR are both average.<br><br>Advantages:  Gnomes have one of the best and most uncrowded newbie zones in the game if you ask me.  Plus, they just look cool and I hear they get all the chicks.<br><br>Disadvantages:  Gnomes have low CHA which may be tough to deal with.  Also, some people may not like starting in such a tucked away corner of Norrath.<br><br>High Elf - INT 102, CHA 90, STA 65, STR 55.  HEs have good INT, and the highest of all CHA.  STA and STR, however, are both very low.<br><br>Advantages:  HEs have excellent starting core stats (INT and CHA) for Enchanters.  They start in a decent area of the world also.<br><br>Disadvantages:  Personally, I really don't like the look or the 'goody-goody' reputation of HEs.  Also, the low STA and STR could be a nuisance.<br><br>Humans - INT 85, CHA 85, STA 75, STR 75.  Humans have the lowest INT, good CHA, and the highest STA and STR.<br><br>Advantages:  Humans can start in Freeport (also in Qeynos I believe but I would rather start in FP) which is a good place to grow up.  Despite the low INT, they are the most 'balanced' race with decent stats everywhere else.<br><br>Disadvantages:  Humans also have no form of night vision to start with.  Of course, the low INT may be a factor as well.  Also, I personally think they are ugly.<br><br>Well, there you have it.  Keep in mind this is by no means a comprehensive comparison nor is it all objective.  Much of it has to do with personal opinion.  The bottom line, decide what's most important to you how you want to play the game and decide based on that what race you will play.  Any race can make an excellent enchanter with all the gear available out there.  The most crucial factor is the ability of the player behind the character.<br><br>Most importantly, have fun!<br><br>-Yizz<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
