<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=10137351633048></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f10137351633048><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=13&mid=10137351633048>RE: life of the cahnter</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=13&mid=10137351633048#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=43653><span id=Scholar>GLASS</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>161 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Feb 14th 8:06 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.70]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>At level 12 you'll run into a lot of people new to the game.&nbsp;&nbsp;So, many, if not most, of them will not know what an enchanter is for yet.  There's a few things you can do.  You could be insistent and keep pounding away at them with speeches about what mezz is and why you don't attack the Orc that's just standing there doing nothing.  If they don't eventually get it, I suppose you could even go so far as disbanding from the group and trying to find a new one.<br><br>Secondly, you could shrug it off after the second or third mezz is broken in a row and stick to debuffing/dotting the MOBs.  Maybe this is just deferring the problem until some other unfortunate enchanter has to teach these guys, but it would be easier on your own sanity for the time being.<br><br>Lastly, you could go find a good place to solo for the next few levels.  If I recall correctly, from 12 to 16, and possibly even up to 20, your animation pet is still reasonably able to take some hits and survive to tank for you while you sit back and debuff/nuke/dot the MOBs to death.<br><br>At level 12, though, I wouldn't get too worked up about it.  People tend to get much better about assisting the main tank as time goes on.  Myself, I was probably around 19 before I ever even grouped with an enchanter.  I learned fast, though, and in fact that group is what made me decide to play an enchanter.  Now, he is my main.  There will still be people down the road who just don't seem to get it though.  I've run into one horrible druid as late as level 39 or so who still didn't understand mez, even after I tried to patiently explain it to him.  His name is now on the list of people who I will not group with again.  Fortunately, this list is not too long yet.  So, be patient, by the time you hit level 20 or so you should be more sought after in groups and you should also find yourself running into less people who don't understand mez and /assist.<br><br>As for spells, it sounds like you've got a pretty good arrangement for yourself.  Tash should always be your opening spell, for obvious reasons.  Personally, at level 41, slow is almost always the second spell I cast also.  The STR debuff is probably nice for now, but soon it won't make enough of a difference for it to be worthwhile.  That's my opinion anyhow.  As far as using the chain stun as a substitute for mez, I say if they can't learn to use mez, then why bother with crowd control at all?  Not to say that chain stunning itself is a bad thing, but not as a substitute for mez in bad groups.  Let them learn from having three MOBs running around smacking everyone around a bit.  <br><br>As for using your DoT (Choke) at that level, it depends on the situation.  If MOBs are surviving long enough for the DoT to run its course or at least long enough to do more than 50 damage, then by all means use the DoT.  If you are in a group that is mowing through MOBs left and right, why not just use your level 8 nuke (Chaotic Feedback) which is 5 less mana.  It only hits for 48, whereas your DoT does 80 total, but again if MOBs aren't staying alive long enough, then your DoT is not worth it.<br><br>I've done this before, and I'm not sure if it helped anyone, but I'll list what spells I'd have memmed at level 12 as a suggestion.  People play differently, though, and this is just what I would have, not necessarily the only spells to use.<br><br>1)Tashan<br>2)Languid Pace<br>3)Choke<br>4)Mesmerise<br>5)Color Flux<br>6)Chaotic Feedback<br>7)Root<br>8)Rotating Buff Slot (Pet, Mist, Lesser Shielding)<br><br>This is actually very similar to what my spells look like even now at level 41 for group situations.  Only difference is Nuke in slot 3 and another Color Stun in slot 6.  I don't know why that matters, just thought I'd mention it.<br><br>OK, that's enough for now.  Hopefully this will give you some ideas though.  Good luck.<br><br>[41 Enchanter] Yizzelar (Unknown)<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
