	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hi there, just wanted to say something about the Jewel craft issue. I am a 250 master Jeweler lvl 59 enchanter. Spend the money and the time to become a 250 Jeweler, but don't do this all at once. Spend time each bringing you skill up 5 to 10 points each level and try and bring your skill up. Don't try and sell any silver rings or anything like that,just make them and sell them back to the merchant. Remember you DO NOT need to enchant the metal in order to increase your skill. You will make money. Once you get one person to buy from you that is lvl 50+ they will pass your name on and so on and so forth. I am not joking when I say I can easily make 10k in one night on jewelry. The people that buy from you will remember you and come back to you, as well as sending their friends to you. Trust me work on it while you are lower in levels and once you are 50+ and can reach skill 250 it pays off big time. <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
