	   <tr><td colspan=2>I agree with you on some points there Ellon, but I don't think you need to be quite so negative in some of your criticisms.&nbsp;&nbsp;Having said that, this is not a flame post, it's a 'response' in the hopes that other people will see that there are more than one side to many issues, and learn to explore and adventure on their own.  Making up their own minds about what works for them.<br><br>1)Jewelry:  Couldn't agree more.  Although I've not completely given up the trade yet, it's become so expensive and cost-ineffecient for me that I've decided to hold it off indefinitely.  With a skill now of 124 I have had only marginal success in selling items like silver ruby veils.  It seems, also, that with every expansion that equipment comes around that is frequently as good or better than what we can make, and usually sells for cheaper.  My advice, maybe practice up jewelry enough to make yourself and friends some cheap silver items in the early levels.  Beyond that, I would wait until you have plenty of plat in the bank, and your INT well over 200 to minimize failures and maximize chances for skill improves.  Otherwise, you'll be Everbroke.<br><br>2)Soloing:  One reason I love my enchanter is that they can be effectively played solo, partnered, or grouped.  For me, I do all three.  Having burned through the last 8 levels or so in OT I am extremely bored with outdoor groups and need a huge change.  So, I've been soloing through level 40.  Could I get better xp in a full group in OT or DL?  Probably, but would I be enjoying myself?  Nope.  It bothers me when people express opinions in the form of 'these are the facts.'  The truth is, enchanters have so many spells and so many unique spells, there is no 'one right way' to play one.  Therefore, IMHO, make up your own mind.  We are capable of soloing, we are highly sought after in groups.  You choose.<br><br>3)Yes, what will define you as a competent enchanter in groups is your ability to keep total control over what is going on.  If you can successfully learn this skill, you will find yourself making lots of friends who will send you tells from three zones away asking you to come group with them.  Your CC abilities save your tanks hitpoints which save your healers mana which allows you to pull faster and get more xp, not to mention to run a very safe group.<br><br>4)Only thing I would add here is check out the enchanter forums on castersrealm.com and ask about Eugee's enchanter guide.  It's very comprehensive, entertaining, and popular.<br><br>So I guess the only point I really didn't see eye to eye with Ellon on were his remarks on soloing.  Other than that, I agree on everything else.  One last comment though, it's kind of ironic that you take offense at the slang terms for clarity, and yet at the bottom of your post you have &quot;Pimping is a state of mind...&quot;  It's a game, don't take it too seriously.<br><br>-Yizzelar<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
