	   <tr><td colspan=2>Not that I dont beleive in the importance of CHA, after all how is it good to have more mana but of bunch of resist on your mez, but CHA gears are simply cheaper. I've put all my points in CHA and now it cost me a fortune to increase my INT. Example on my server a batskull earring cost 300pp-450pp and it gives +5 INT but an opalline earring cost like 80pp for 5 CHA. For about 140pp you can make yourself a pair of +7 CHA ring and i think its trivial at 127, for a pair of +5 INT you'd need Velium rings which cost way much more. You can make yourself a pair of +7 CHA bracer for about 25pp once you can enchant gold and I personnaly dont know any +7 INT items that you can get for that price. Even if you dont have the money to learn jewelry those items are pretty cheap for the CHA they provides and anyone with a skill of 150 can make it easily. So for +38 CHA it could only cost you 350pp (well on my server) it probly cost me 3k for the same amount of INT gears. It cost me about 1.5k to get my jewelry skill to 150 so my advice to you is put your points in INT and make up with the gears. And also you will get CHA buff later that will totally make up for the CHA you dont have when you start.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
